            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "In that case an absolute recommendation for Python 3 might not be in place. Currently however the docs ([this page](http://flask.pocoo.org/docs/python3/) in particular) basically say:\nDon't use python 3, in theory you can use it, but basically no libraries on PyPi support it and if you have a question you cannot Google it. \n\nThis was the case a year ago when the last changes where made. This is not the case any more though. I really think it's important for big projects like this to at least be a bit positive about Python 3 to increase adoption.\n"
