            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "To be clear I'm not opposed to making any changes and apparently an update is in fact necessary to keep it accurate. \n\nWe shouldn't say \"Python 3 is bad, don't use it\". We should focus on the issues that exist and make a conservative recommendation based on that. People should then be able to make a well informed decision based on that. \n\nFor example if you are new, learning Python/Flask and want to use Python 3 for your personal site, a great many of the issues with Python 3 probably won't apply, so it's fine if you choose to go that route and you shouldn't feel pressured to use Python 2. \n"
        },
